@NODE MAIN "PolyEd ｷ ARexx commands"

                       PolyEd's ARexx commands

                   Copyright ｩ 1994,95 Avalon UnLtd.
                      Written by Robert Brandner
                         All Rights Reserved


Like every good program, PolyEd provides an ARexx Port. This guide
describes all ARexx commands, PolyEd supports. For details about
results, naming of ports etc. see the main guide (it's name depends
on your preferred language).

Sorry, this guide is - at the moment - only available in english.


 Project-Related Commands

@{" NEW            " LINK AREXX_NEW}	@{" OPEN           " LINK AREXX_OPEN}	@{" SAVE           " LINK AREXX_SAVE}
@{" SAVEAS         " LINK AREXX_SAVEAS}	@{" CLOSE          " LINK AREXX_CLOSE}	@{" PRINT          " LINK AREXX_PRINT}
@{" QUIT           " LINK AREXX_QUIT}

 Block-Related Commands

@{" BLOCK          " LINK AREXX_BLOCK}	@{" CUT            " LINK AREXX_CUT}	@{" COPY           " LINK AREXX_COPY}
@{" PASTE          " LINK AREXX_PASTE}	@{" ERASE          " LINK AREXX_ERASE}

 Cursor Positioning Commands

@{" GOTOLINE       " LINK AREXX_GOTOLINE}	@{" GOTOCOLUMN     " LINK AREXX_GOTOCOLUMN}	@{" CURSOR         " LINK AREXX_CURSOR}
@{" LINE           " LINK AREXX_LINE}	@{" COLUMN         " LINK AREXX_COLUMN}	@{" POSITION       " LINK AREXX_POSITION}
@{" GOTOAUTOMARK   " LINK AREXX_GOTOAUTOMARK}	@{" GETCURSORPOS   " LINK AREXX_GETCURSORPOS}

 Find and Replace Commands

@{" FIND           " LINK AREXX_FIND}	@{" FINDCHANGE     " LINK AREXX_FINDCHANGE}	@{" FINDNEXT       " LINK AREXX_FINDNEXT}
@{" FINDPREVIOUS   " LINK AREXX_FINDPREVIOUS}

 Text-Related Commands

@{" BACKSPACE      " LINK AREXX_BACKSPACE}	@{" DELETE         " LINK AREXX_DELETE}	@{" GETCHAR        " LINK AREXX_GETCHAR}
@{" GETLINE        " LINK AREXX_GETLINE}	@{" GETWORD        " LINK AREXX_GETWORD}	@{" TEXT           " LINK AREXX_TEXT}
@{" UNDO           " LINK AREXX_UNDO}	@{" REDO           " LINK AREXX_REDO}

 Window-Related Commands

@{" MOVEWINDOW     " LINK AREXX_MOVEWINDOW}	@{" SIZEWINDOW     " LINK AREXX_SIZEWINDOW}	@{" CHANGEWINDOW   " LINK AREXX_CHANGEWINDOW}
@{" WINDOWTOFRONT  " LINK AREXX_WINDOWTOFRONT}	@{" WINDOWTOBACK   " LINK AREXX_WINDOWTOBACK}	@{" ACTIVATEWINDOW " LINK AREXX_ACTIVATEWINDOW}
@{" ZOOMWINDOW     " LINK AREXX_ZOOMWINDOW}	@{" UNZOOMWINDOW   " LINK AREXX_UNZOOMWINDOW}

 Miscellaneous Commands

@{" LOCKGUI        " LINK AREXX_LOCKGUI}	@{" UNLOCKGUI      " LINK AREXX_UNLOCKGUI}	@{" GETATTR        " LINK AREXX_GETATTR}
@{" SETATTR        " LINK AREXX_SETATTR}	@{" LEARN          " LINK AREXX_LEARN}

@ENDNODE #######################################################################


@NODE AREXX_ACTIVATEWINDOW "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - ACTIVATEWINDOW"

ACTIVATEWINDOW
   ,

ACTIVATEWINDOW activates the first window of the project.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_BACKSPACE "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - BACKSPACE"

BACKSPACE
   SOW/S,SOL/S

BACKSPACE deletes the character left to the cursor. At the beginning
of a line, the EOL character of the previous line is deleted, and so
the previous and the current line are joined.

 ｷ SOW deletes to the start of the current word.
 ｷ SOL deletes to the start of the current line.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

----------------------------------------

@NODE AREXX_BLOCK "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - BLOCK"

BLOCK
   START/S,FORGET/S

BLOCK starts or forgets block selection.

 ｷ START starts block selection. Following cursor movements will
   select the block. Then you may CUT, COPY or ERASE the block.
 ｷ FORGET forgets selection.

Inserting or deleting text, or any mouse actions by the user, 
have the same effect as BLOCK FORGET, So you should @{"LOCKGUI" Link AREXX_LOCKGUI}, to
avoid unwanted actions by the user.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_CHANGEWINDOW "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - CHANGEWINDOW"

CHANGEWINDOW
   LEFTEDGE/N,TOPEDGE/N,WIDTH/N,HEIGHT/N

CHANGEWINDOW changes the position and size of the first window of 
the project.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_CLOSE "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - CLOSE"

CLOSE
   FORCE/S

CLOSE closes the project and its window(s). If the project has been 
modified, the modified project requester comes up, asking the user if 
he wants to save the project first. 

 ｷ FORCE suppresses the modified project requester.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_COLUMN "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - COLUMN"

COLUMN
   DELTA/N/A

COLUMN accepts positive and negative values, to move the cursor left or 
right relative to its current position.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_COPY "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - COPY"

COPY 
   ,

COPY places a duplicate of the currently selected block into the 
clipboard.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_CURSOR "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - CURSOR"

CURSOR
   UP/S,DOWN/S,LEFT/S,RIGHT/S

CURSOR moves the cursor up, down, left or right a single line or
column position.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_CUT "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - CUT"

CUT
   LINE/S,EOL/S

CUT removes the currently selected block from the project, and places
it in the clipboard.

 ｷ LINE cuts the current line (incl. EOL)
 ｷ EOL cuts from current cursor position to end of line (excl. EOL)
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_DELETE "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - DELETE"

DELETE
   EOW/S,EOL/S

DELETE removes the character right to the cursor.

 ｷ EOW deletes to the end of the current word.
 ｷ EOL deletes to the end of line. In contrary to CUT EOL, DELETE EOL
   does not copy the deleted text to the clipboard.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_ERASE "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - ERASE"

ERASE
   ,

ERASE removes the selected block from the project.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_FIND "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - FIND"

FIND
   PROMPT/S,NEXT/S,PREVIOUS/S,TEXT/F

FIND searches for text that matches the specified text.

 ｷ PROMPT opens the Find requester, but does not search.
 ｷ NEXT searches for the next occurence of findstring.
 ｷ PREVIOUS searches for the previous occurence of findstring.
 ｷ TEXT sets findstring to specified text.

'FIND NEXT' finds the next occurence of whatever findstring is.
'FIND foobar' sets findstring to 'foobar' but does not search.
'FIND NEXT foobar' sets findstring to 'foobar' and searches.
'FIND PROMPT' opens the Find requester.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_FINDCHANGE "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - FINDCHANGE"

FINDCHANGE
   FINDCHANGE PROMPT/S,FIND/K,CHANGE/K,ALL/S

Searches for text and replaces it by another text. This is done  like 
replace from the menu, i. e. if the selected block matches findstring 
it is replaced by changestring, else nothing is done. Then the next 
occurence of findstring is selected. 

 ｷ PROMPT opens the Find & Change requester, but does not search.
 ｷ FIND sets findstring to specified text.
 ｷ CHANGE sets changestring to specified text.
 ｷ ALL searches and changes from current cursor position to end
   of text.

'FINDCHANGE FIND foobar CHANGE hello' sets findstring to 'foobar',
changestring to 'hello' and does a find & replace.
'FINDCHANGE' does a find & replace with current findstring
and changestring.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_FINDNEXT "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - FINDNEXT"

FINDNEXT
   ,

FINDNEXT finds the next occurence of findstring.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_FINDPREVIOUS "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - FINDPREVIOUS"

FINDPREVIOUS
   ,

FINDPREVIOUS finds the previous occurence of findstring.	
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_GETATTR "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - GETATTR"

GETATTR
   OBJECT/A,NAME,FIELD

GETATTR obtains information about the attributes of an object.

 ｷ OBJECT specifies the object type to obtain information on.
 ｷ NAME specifies the name of the object.
 ｷ FIELD spceifies which field should be checked for information.

In the above OBJECT you may seek information an the attributes of 
any of the following items:

 ｷ APPLICATION
 ｷ PROJECTS
 ｷ PROJECT <name>
 ｷ MACROS
 ｷ MACRO <name>

If the destination variable is a stem variable, the following fields 
are available:

APPLICATION consists of the following nodes (an aspect of APPLICATION
you can seek sub-information about):

 ｷ VERSION 		Contains the current version information.
 ｷ SCREEN		Contains the name of the public screen, 
			PolyEd resides in.
 ｷ CURRENT		Contains the name of current project's
			arexx port.
 ｷ AREXX		Contains the name of PolyEd's global port.
 ｷ VAR_BLOCKSTARTLINE  	These four nodes ...
 ｷ VAR_BLOCKSTARTCOL	... contain the beginning ...
 ｷ VAR_BLOCKENDLINE	... and end of ...
 ｷ VAR_BLOCKENDCOL	... the selected block.
 ｷ VAR_FINDSTRING	Contains the findstring FIND, FINDCHANGE,
			FINDNEXT and FINDPREVIOUS look for.
 ｷ VAR_CHANGESTRING	Contains the changestring, FINDCHANGE uses.
 ｷ FLAG_IGNORECASE	Contains the status of 'Ignore Case?'.
 ｷ FLAG_WHOLEWORDS	Contains the status of 'Whole Words?'.
 ｷ VAR_ARRANGEMODE	Contains the status of window arrange style
			( 0=stacked, 1=vertical, 2=horizontal, 3=full size )
 ｷ FLAG_LEARNING	Contains the status of 'Learn macro'.
 ｷ VAR_RIGHTBORDER	Contains right border value (from settings).
 ｷ VAR_TABWIDTH		Contains Tab width value (from settings).
 ｷ FLAG_OVERWRITE	Contains the status of 'Overwrite?'.
 ｷ FLAG_AUTOINDENT	Contains the status of 'Auto indent?'.
 ｷ FLAG_TABISSPACES	Contains the status of 'TAB is spaces?'.
 ｷ FLAG_CREATEICONS	Contains the status of 'Create icons?'.
 ｷ VAR_FULLINES		Contains the status of 'Full Lines'
			( 0=ignore, 1=word wrap ).
 ｷ VAR_AUTOSAVE  	Contains the status of 'Auto Save'
			( 0=never, 1=every 5 min, 2=every 10 min, 
			3=every 15 min, 4=every 30 min, 5=every hour ).
 ｷ VAR_BACKUPS		Contains the status of 'Backups'
			( 0=none, 1=last version, 2=infinite ).
 ｷ VAR_SAVEAS		Contains the status of 'Save as'
			( 0=ASCII, 1=IFF FTXT ).

PROJECTS.COUNT contains the number of projects; PROJECTS.0 through 
PROJECTS.n contain the name of the project.

PROJECT consists of the following nodes:

 ｷ AREXX		Contains the ARexx port of the project.
 ｷ FILENAME		Contains the complete filename of the project.
 ｷ PATH			Contains the path portion of the filename.
 ｷ FILE			Contains the file portion of the filename.
 ｷ LINES		Contains the number of lines of the project.
 ｷ CHANGES		Contains the number of cchanges mode to the 
			project (since last save).

MACROS.COUNT contains the number of macros; MACROS.0 through 
MACROS.n contain the name of the macro.

MACRO consists of the following nodes:

 ｷ FILENAME		Contains the filename of the macro.
 ｷ HOTKEY		Contains the macros hotkey.

See the demo program 'getattr.ped' for how to use this complex command.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_GETCHAR "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - GETCHAR"

GETCHAR 
   ,

GETCHAR returns the character right to (or under) the cursor.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_GETCURSORPOS "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - GETCURSORPOS"

GETCURSORPOS 
   ,

GETCURSORPOS returns the position of the cursor. The following nodes 
are returned when using a stem variable:

 ｷ LINE		Contains the line, the cursor is in.
 ｷ COLUMN	Contains the column the cursor is in.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_GETLINE "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - GETLINE"

GETLINE 
   ,

GETLINE returns the contents of the line, under the cursor.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_GETWORD "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - GETWORD"

GETWORD 
   ,

GETWORD returns the word under the cursor.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_GOTOAUTOMARK "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - GOTOAUTOMARK"

GOTOAUTOMARK 
   ,

GOTOAUTOMARK moves to the cursor to the position where the last 
change was made to the project.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_GOTOCOLUMN "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - GOTOCOLUMN"

GOTOCOLUMN
   COLUMN/N/A

GOTOCOLUMN moves the cursor to the specified position.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_GOTOLINE "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - GOTOLINE"

GOTOLINE
   LINE/N/A

GOTOLINE moves the cursor to the specified line.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_LEARN "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - LEARN"

LEARN
   FILE/K,STOP/S

LEARN allows PolyEd to build an ARexx macro consisting of the 
actions the user performs.

 ｷ FILE specifies where the macro is to be saved.
 ｷ STOP tells PolyEd to stop learning.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_LINE "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - LINE"

LINE
   DELTA/N/K

LINE accepts positive or negative arguemtns to move the cursor up or 
down relative to its current position.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_LOCKGUI "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - LOCKGUI"

LOCKGUI 
   ,

LOCKGUI inhibits the graphical user interface of PolyEd.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_MOVEWINDOW "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - MOVEWINDOW"

MOVEWINDOW
   LEFTEDGE/N,TOPEDGE/N

MOVEWINDOW is used to change the position of the first window of the 
project. A value of -1 means no change or don't care.	
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_NEW "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - NEW"

NEW
   ,

NEW creates a new project.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_OPEN "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - OPEN"

OPEN
   FILENAME/K

OPEN opens the specified text into a new project (if there is an
unmodified new project around it will be opened into that).

 ｷ FILENAME specifies the file to be opened.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_PASTE "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - PASTE"

PASTE
   ,

PASTE puts the contents of the clipboard into the project - at the 
cursor position.	
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_POSITION "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - POSITION"

POSITION
   SOF/S,EOF/S,SOL/S,EOL/S,SOW/S,EOW/S,SOV/S,EOV/S

POSITION moves the cursor to the position specified by the argument:
 ｷ SOF moves it to the beginning of the file.
 ｷ EOF moves it to the end of the file.
 ｷ SOL moves it to the beginning of the current line.
 ｷ EOL moves it to the end of the current line.
 ｷ SOW moves it to the start of the current word.
 ｷ EOW moves it to the end of the current word.
 ｷ SOV moves it to the top of the current view.
 ｷ EOV moves it to the end of the current view.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_PRINT "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - PRINT"

PRINT
   FILENAME/K

PRINT prints the contents of the current project. If FILENAME is
set, the text is print to the specified file instead of the printer.

 ｷ FILENAME specifies a file where the text shall be printed to.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_QUIT "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - QUIT"

QUIT
   FORCE/S

QUIT ends PolyEd. For every modified project a modified project 
requester comes up.

 ｷ FORCE suppresses the modified project requesters.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_REDO "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - REDO"

REDO 
   ,

REDO allows you to undo the @{"UNDO" LINK AREXX_UNDO} command.	
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_SAVE "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - SAVE"

SAVE 
   ,

SAVE saves the current project to its current filename. If the 
project is unnamed, a file requester comes up, asking the user for a 
name for the project.	
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_SAVEAS "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - SAVEAS"

SAVEAS
   NAME/K 

This command saves the current project to the specified filename. If
no name is specified, a file requester comes up, asking the user for
a filename for the project.

 ｷ NAME specifies the name to that the project should be saved. The
   name should be placed in quotes.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_SETATTR "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - SETATTR"

SETATTR
   OBJECT/A,NAME,FIELD,NEWVALUE

SETATTR manipulates the aspects of an object.

 ｷ OBJECT specifies the object type to manipulate.
 ｷ NAME specifies the handle of the object.
 ｷ FIELD specifies which field should be modified.
 ｷ NEWVALUE specifies the new value for that field. Watch out; some
   fields require numeric values, some require strings.

In the above OBJECT you may set attributes of any of the following items:

 ｷ APPLICATION
 ｷ PROJECT <name>

Valid values for FLAG_xxx fields are 0 and 1, where
0 means no/off/false and 1 means yes/on/true.
All modifications are immediately made visible to the user.

If OBJECT is APPLICATION the following fields may be manipulated:

 ｷ VAR_FINDSTRING	findstring for FIND, FINDCHANGE,
 			FINDNEXT and FINDPREVIOUS
 ｷ VAR_CHANGESTRING	changestring for FINDCHANGE
 ｷ FLAG_IGNORECASE	status of 'Ignore Case?'.
 ｷ FLAG_WHOLEWORDS	status of 'Whole Words?'.
 ｷ VAR_ARRANGEMODE	status of window arrange style
			( 0=stacked, 1=vertical, 2=horizontal, 3=full size )
 ｷ VAR_RIGHTBORDER	right border value
 ｷ VAR_TABWIDTH		Tab width value
 ｷ FLAG_OVERWRITE	status of 'Overwrite?'.
 ｷ FLAG_AUTOINDENT	status of 'Auto indent?'.
 ｷ FLAG_TABISSPACES	status of 'TAB is spaces?'.
 ｷ FLAG_WORDWRAP	status of 'Wordwrap?'
 ｷ FLAG_CREATEICONS	status of 'Create icons?'.


If OBJECT is PROJECT the following fields may be manipulated:

 ｷ FLAG_HIDDEN 		0=Reveal project, 1=Hide project


Examples:
'SETATTR APPLICATION FIELD VAR_TABWIDTH NEWVALUE 6' sets the Tab Width to 6.
'SETATTR APPLICATION FIELD FLAG_WORDWRAP NEWVALUE 1' activates Wordwrap.
'SETATTR APPLICATION FIELD VAR_FINDSTRING NEWVALUE foobar' lets further searches
 look for foobar.
'SETATTR APPLICATION FIELD CURRENTPROJECT NEWVALUE foobar' makes the project
 named foobar the current one.
'SETATTR PROJECT foobar FLAG_HIDDEN 1' hides project foobar.
'SETATTR PROJECT foobar FLAG_HIDDEN 0' reveals project foobar.

@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_SIZEWINDOW "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - SIZEWINDOW"

SIZEWINDOW
   WIDTH/N,HEIGHT/N

SIZEWINDOW allows to change the size of the project's first window.	
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_TEXT "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - TEXT"

TEXT
   NEWLINE/S,TEXT/F

TEXT inserts the specified text at the current cursor position of 
the project.

 ｷ NEWLINE begins a new line _before_ the text is inserted.
 ｷ TEXT specifies the text to be inserted. If the text contains 
   spaces, or if there are spaces at the beginning or end of the 
   text, you should explicitly use the keyword, because otherwise 
   leading and trailing spaces are stripped off by the arugment 
   parser.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_UNDO "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - UNDO"

UNDO
   ,

UNDO undoes actions of the user. UNDO can be undone by @{"REDO" LINK AREXX_REDO}.
See also menu item  'Edit/Undo'.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################
	
@NODE AREXX_UNLOCKGUI "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - UNLOCKGUI"

UNLOCKGUI
   ,	

UNLOCKGUI undoes @{"LOCKGUI" LINK AREXX_LOCKGUI} allowing GUI events to resume.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_UNZOOMWINDOW "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - UNZOOMWINDOW"

UNZOOMWINDOW
   ,

UNZOOMWINDOW unshrinks the project's first window (see @{"ZOOMWINDOW" LINK AREXX_ZOOMWINDOW}).
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_WINDOWTOBACK "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - WINDOWTOBACK"

WINDOWTOBACK
   ,

WINDOWTOBACK moves the project's first window behind all other windows.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_WINDOWTOFRONT "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - WINDOWTOFRONT"

WINDOWTOFRONT
   ,

WINDOWTOFRONT moves the project's first window in front of all other 
windows.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE AREXX_ZOOMWINDOW "PolyEd ｷ ARexx - ZOOMWINDOW"

ZOOMWINDOW
   ,	

ZOOMWINDOW makes the project's first window very small. Use 
@{"UNZOOMWINDOW" LINK AREXX_UNZOOMWINDOW} to unshrink it again.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################
